# Thesis Appendix A, Test 2 - Short Circuit Current (Listing 9)
# GaAs pn photodetector: 1.0 cm total length, p-side Na=1e17 cm-3, n-side Nd=3e17 cm-3
# p-region: 0 to 0.5 cm (Na=1e17), n-region: 0.5 to 1.0 cm (Nd=3e17)
#
# NOTE: Lengths are in cm (NUMERIC internal units), not microns.
#
# OPTICAL SETUP - configure via GUI (Environment > Optical Input):
#   - Enable "Enable Optical Generation" checkbox
#   - Add spectral component: Photon Energy = 2.0 eV, Intensity = 0.1 W/cm2
#     (corresponds to 100 mW/cm2 at 620.7 nm wavelength, above GaAs bandgap ~1.42 eV)
#   - Alternatively: load the companion spectrum file test/gaas_photodetector.spc
#   - "Left-side Incident Light" and "Spectrum Over Entire Device" are on by default
# After configuring optical input, run Simulate (Device > Start Simulation / F5).
#
# Expected result (thesis reference):
#   Jsc = 12.1 mA/cm2  (short-circuit photocurrent)
#   Analytical estimate: 11.6 mA/cm2  (~4% error, acceptable)

grid length=.45 points=100
grid length=.1 points=200
grid length=.45 points=100

structure length=1.00 material=gaas

doping length=.5 Na=1e17
doping length=.5 Nd=3e17

region length=1.00 bulk
